                            <comment id="17483730" author="tallison@mitre.org" created="Fri, 28 Jan 2022 11:56:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What is the recommended fix for this?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17483739" author="JIRAUSER280439" created="Fri, 28 Jan 2022 12:09:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Need to upgrade on XercesJ version 2.12.2&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17483750" author="tallison@mitre.org" created="Fri, 28 Jan 2022 12:38:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Was that recently released? I don&#8217;t see it yet here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/xerces/xercesImpl&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/xerces/xercesImpl&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17483777" author="JIRAUSER280439" created="Fri, 28 Jan 2022 13:35:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It is not available on maven, however here is the release details&#160; from xerces - &lt;a href=&quot;https://xerces.apache.org/xerces2-j/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://xerces.apache.org/xerces2-j/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17483793" author="tallison@mitre.org" created="Fri, 28 Jan 2022 14:05:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We have to wait for that to hit a maven repo before we can upgrade.  @dependabot should let us know.  We&apos;re on the cusp of starting the 2.3.0 release process.  I think we should wait for this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That said, if you&apos;re running Tika on untrusted data, you need to defend against infinite loops and other disasters.  You can use the stuff we&apos;ve build or harden your own wrapper.  See: &lt;a href=&quot;https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/TIKA/The+Robustness+of+Apache+Tika&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/TIKA/The+Robustness+of+Apache+Tika&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
